SIMPLE: eloquent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eloquent
<hw>El"o*quent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧loquent</ets>, L. <ets>eloquens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>,
p. pr. of <ets>eloqui</ets> to speak out, declaim; <ets>e</ets> +
<ets>loqui</ets> to speak. See <er>Loquacious</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having the power of expressing strong emotions or forcible
arguments in an elevated, impassioned, and effective manner; <as>as, an
<ex>eloquent</ex> orator or preacher</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O Death, all-<qex>eloquent</qex>! You only prove⟦br⟧
What dust we dote on when 't is man we love.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Adapted to express strong emotion or to state facts
arguments with fluency and power; <as>as, an <ex>eloquent</ex> address
or statement; an <ex>eloquent</ex> appeal to a jury.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eloquently</ent>⟦br⟧
